    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-01-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="358" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Strobel</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-01-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7,
                            1890</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 47.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received Mr. Palmer’s No. 35 of the
                        16th ultimo, reporting that, in compliance with my No. 37 of November 25,
                        last, he had addressed notes to the Spanish Government in regard to the
                        indemnity claimed by the Rev. Mr. Doane for his imprisonment and to the
                        threatened seizure of the lands of his mission by the governor of
                        Ponape.</p>
                <p>His action is approved.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
